From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: tim2tox-bootstrap <bootstrap@local>
Date: Wed, 20 May 2026 07:25:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 8/8] _handleGlobalCallback: also pass through GroupTipsEvent
 to singleton listener

Mirror of 0004's FriendAddRequest dual-fire for the group-tips channel.

`NativeLibraryManager._handleGlobalCallback` already dispatches every
incoming callback to the platform via
`platform.dispatchInstanceGlobalCallback(...)` when an `instance_id` is
present, and for non-zero instance it early-returns so the SDK's own
singleton handler doesn't double-fire. The only exception was
`FriendAddRequest`, which was deliberately allowed to fall through so
that callers who register friendship listeners through the SDK
singleton (`TIMFriendshipManager.instance.addFriendListener`) still
receive friend requests on multi-instance test runs.

Group listeners had the same architectural mismatch but no
fall-through. tim2tox auto_tests and toxee both register group
listeners via `TIMGroupManager.instance.addGroupListener` (which goes
into the SDK singleton's `v2TimGroupListenerList`, not into
`Tim2ToxSdkPlatform._instanceGroupListeners`). When a Tox group invite
arrived on a non-zero instance:

  1. The platform's `dispatchInstanceGlobalCallback` was called.
  2. Inside `GroupTipsEvent`, `grpList = _instanceGroupListeners[id]
     ?? []` was empty (no platform-side registration), so it hit
     `if (grpList.isEmpty) break;` and dropped the event.
  3. `_handleGlobalCallback` then early-returned without calling
     `_groupListener?.onMemberInvited(...)`.

Result: every multi-node Phase 4 (Group) virtual scenario that
expected `onGroupInvited` / `onMemberInvited` / `onGroupCreated` /
`onMemberEnter` timed out in `setUpAll`, even though the C++ side was
firing the callback correctly. Eight of ten group virtual tests were
affected (group_message, group_invite, group_double_invite,
group_state, group_sync, group_topic_revert, group_moderation, group).
The two that passed (group_save, group_topic) don't rely on group
callbacks.

Fix: extend the existing fall-through allowlist to also cover
`GlobalCallbackType.GroupTipsEvent`. The platform handler still runs
first; if it has its own platform-registered listeners it fires them
and the singleton fire is a no-op (the singleton `_groupListener` is
typically the SDK's internal fan-out which respects its own list). If
it has none (the toxee/auto_tests case), the singleton path fires
correctly.

A small `passthroughCallbacks` set is introduced so future additions
to the dual-fire list don't keep growing the conditional. Behavior is
unchanged for FriendAddRequest.
---
 .../bindings/native_library_manager.dart      | 20 +++++++++++++++----
 1 file changed, 17 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/lib/native_im/bindings/native_library_manager.dart b/lib/native_im/bindings/native_library_manager.dart
--- a/lib/native_im/bindings/native_library_manager.dart
+++ b/lib/native_im/bindings/native_library_manager.dart
@@ -366,10 +366,24 @@
     if (instanceId != null && platform.isCustomPlatform) {
       platform.dispatchInstanceGlobalCallback(
           instanceId, callbackType, dataFromNativeMap);
-      // For non-zero instance, only fall through for FriendAddRequest so
-      // _friendshipListener is also called (matches 8.7 tim2tox behavior).
-      if (instanceId != 0 &&
-          callbackType != GlobalCallbackType.FriendAddRequest.value) {
+      // For non-zero instance, fall through for a small set of callbacks so the
+      // SDK's singleton `_friendshipListener` / `_groupListener` are also called.
+      // This matches the 8.7 tim2tox behavior and is required for clients (and
+      // auto_tests) that register listeners via `TIMFriendshipManager.instance.
+      // addFriendListener` / `TIMGroupManager.instance.addGroupListener` instead
+      // of the platform's per-instance addGroupListener (which is the typical
+      // toxee + auto_tests pattern).
+      //
+      // Without GroupTipsEvent in this list, the multi-instance test path
+      // (Tim2ToxSdkPlatform.dispatchInstanceGlobalCallback) early-returns on
+      // `grpList.isEmpty` and the event is lost — tests waiting for
+      // onGroupInvited / onMemberInvited / onGroupCreated time out.
+      const passthroughCallbacks = <int>{};
+      final shouldPassthrough = callbackType ==
+              GlobalCallbackType.FriendAddRequest.value ||
+          callbackType == GlobalCallbackType.GroupTipsEvent.value ||
+          passthroughCallbacks.contains(callbackType);
+      if (instanceId != 0 && !shouldPassthrough) {
         return;
       }
     }
